Flushing Meadow Park (Queens): Shown, under construction, are the Corona gates of the New York World's Fair, 1939-40, on the east side of 111th Street between 50th and 53rd Avenues.

View 1 is south on 111th Street; note the two steel prows of the Marine Industry Building.

May 30, 1938
Views 1,2

Flushing Meadow Park (Queens): One of the gates to the grounds of the World's Fair 1939-40, on the east side of 111th Street at 50th Avenue. The Fair's theme--the Trylon and Perisphere--appears on the right; in view 2 appear the Railroads Building (left), part of the general Motors Building (right), and World's Fair buses of the Fifth Avenue Coach Company.

June 23, 1940
Views 1,2

P. L. Sperr
